Top on the list is the 2022 Commonwealth Games in Birmingham, the next Olympic Games in 2024 and the next All African Games in 2022 in Bamako are crucial for the once dreaded boxing team.Boxing Federation of Kenya President Anthony “Jamal” Otieno who was elected in June last year seemed to have started work on a good footing before Covid-19 disrupted local sports. It has been a tough season for boxing in Kenya with no fireworks in the ring, thanks to the coronavirus pandemic.
The whole boxing calendar  could not withstand the devastating blow from the deadly virus and was knocked down.
As the “Hit Squad”, Kenya’s national boxing team, prepares to punch back after Covid-19 drawback, is clear that  2020 proved a tough boxing year for the national team.



