Kenya's Christine Ongare poses for photos after her unanimous points decision victory over Uganda’s Catherine Nanziri in the flyweight box-off to become the first Kenyan woman boxer to qualify for the Olympics through a competitive qualifier on February 29, 2020.
Photo credit: Pool


Even before the deadly pandemic unleashed a devastating blow that disrupted global sports, all was not well at the “Hit Squad” camp.
Kenya competed in the African qualifiers for the Olympics in Dakar, Senegal, from February 20 - 28, and the verdict was that the team was not ready for the Olympic contest.
Kenya’s performance at the imposing Dakar International Expo Centre in Diamniadio was below par. It was evident the residential training camp the team attended  in Nanyuki under coach Musa Benjamin did not produce the magic spark.



