Only two boxers made the cut for the Olympics. Team captain, featherweight Nick Okoth, and female boxer flyweight Christine Ongare won their slots. Shaffi Bakari (flyweight), Boniface Mogunde (welter), Humphrey Ochieng (light-heavy), Joseph Shighali (lightweight), Elly Ajowi (heavy), Fred Ramogi (super heavy) and Rayton Okwiri (middleweight) fell by the wayside.





Featherweight Nick Okoth works out on March 20, 2020 at St Teresa's Social Hall.
Photo credit: Chris Omollo | Nation Media Group


The women squad also got a devastating blow. Those who kissed the canvas include Elizabeth Andiego (middle), Elizabeth Akinyi (welter), Everlyne Akinyi (lightweight), Beatrice Akoth (feather).
At least 37 African boxers won their bouts to qualify for the postponed Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games which will be held next year.



