While Okwiri is determined to win  an Olympics slot, policeman Gicharu has since thrown in the towel to concentrate on coaching budding pugilists in Nairobi.










Olympian Rayton Okwiri during a training session at the Kaloleni Social Hall on December 11, 2019.
Photo credit: File | Nation Media Group


Tokyo Olympics was scheduled for July 24-August 9 but was postponed due to coronavirus pandemic which halted sporting activities to a halt.
As the “Hit Squad” prepares to push for more slots in the Tokyo Games, 2021 will be full of activities as the squad prepares for three major international events.
Top on the list is the 2022 Commonwealth Games in Birmingham, the next Olympic Games in 2024 and the next All African Games in 2022 in Bamako are crucial for the once dreaded boxing team.
Boxing Federation of Kenya President Anthony “Jamal” Otieno who was elected in June last year seemed to have started work on a good footing before Covid-19 disrupted local sports.
Otieno’s contribution to the game  remains to be seen in the new year.
